We should generally avoid `@cython.locals()` and `@cython.returns()` and use type annotations instead.
```suggestion
@cython.cfunc
def c_compare(a: cython.int, b: cython.int) -> cython.bint:
```

Semantics-wise, we need to make the function a `cfunc` first, then we can attach an `exceptval`.
```suggestion
@cython.exceptval(-1)
@cython.cfunc
```
